	<h1 class="highlight">ETHICS OF A PASTOR AND MINISTER IN KINGDOM DIPLOMATS</h1>
	<h2>MORAL STANDARDS AND MINISTERIAL </h2>
	<p>Being a Pastor/ Minister is the extension of the representation and ministry office of Jesus Christ to the body/Local assembly and goes with high standards of consecrations, holiness, sanctification, and righteousness.
	Scriptures are standards for the moral values and ethics of the Pastors/Ministers of Kingdom Diplomats. Some of the key scriptures are: Titus 1:5-9, 1 Timothy 3: 1-16, 1 Peter 5:1-4.
Disciplined/self-control.</p>

<h2>DRESSING</h2>
<p>	
•	A Pastor/ Minsters dressing should be moderate communicating decency and responsibility wherever His/her is found 
•	Pastors/ Minister are expected to dress corporate to every service in the church
•	wearing shoes for every service
•	Haircuts/styles must be moderate and not communicate wildness
•	Dressing to Pastoral council meetings, Operations meetings, and general meetings must be formal. ( Casual outfit is not acceptable) 
</p>
<div class="mainpoint highlight">see- through dresses, off-shoulders, sleeveless, miniskirts, and trousers are not permitted for any service or program for female ministers </div>

